# Job Naming Rules

Pattern

```text id="1f7ev7"
<Action><Entity>Job
```

Examples

ProcessWebhookJob

RetryWebhookJob

SyncOrdersJob

SendNotificationJob

CleanupOldLogsJob

---

# Job Design Rules

Jobs must be:

- Idempotent
- Retryable
- Observable

---

Jobs must not:

- Depend on HTTP Context
- Depend on UI State

---

# Idempotency Rules

Critical Requirement

Jobs may execute multiple times.

Same job must not:

- Duplicate cashback
- Duplicate notifications
- Duplicate balance updates

---

# Retry Rules

Transient failures should retry.

Examples

Provider API Failure

Database Timeout

Network Error

---

Retries must use exponential backoff.

---

# Webhook Jobs

Recommended Flow

Webhook Received

↓

Store Event

↓

Queue Job

↓

ProcessWebhookJob

↓

Orders Module

---

Webhook controller should remain lightweight.

---

# Notification Jobs

Future Flow

Create Notification

↓

Queue Delivery Job

↓

Send Email

↓

Mark Delivered

---

Notification failures must not affect business logic.

---

# Synchronization Jobs

Examples

SyncAccesstradeOrdersJob

---

Purpose

Verify:

- Missing Orders
- Status Updates
- Commission Updates

---

Synchronization should be read-safe.

---

# Cleanup Jobs

Examples

CleanupAuditLogsJob

CleanupExpiredTokensJob

CleanupWebhookEventsJob

---

Never delete critical financial data.

---

# Scheduling Rules

Recurring Jobs

Examples

Every 5 Minutes

Retry Failed Webhooks

---

Hourly

Sync Orders

---

Daily

Cleanup Tasks

---

Schedule values should be configurable.

---

# Monitoring Rules

Track

- Job Success Rate
- Job Failure Rate
- Retry Count
- Execution Time

---

Admin Dashboard should expose:

Job Health Metrics

---

# Error Handling Rules

Every job failure must be logged.

Store

- Job Name
- Error Message
- Occurred At

---

Never silently swallow exceptions.

---

# Logging Rules

Log

✓ Job Started

✓ Job Completed

✓ Job Failed

✓ Job Retried

---

Never log:

✗ Secrets

✗ Tokens

